# Web Scraper with Node.js & Flask

# Overview
This project scrapes a webpage using Puppeteer (Node.js) and serves the data through an API using Flask (Python). It runs inside a Docker container with a multi-stage build.

# Technologies Used
   Node.js + Puppeteer (for web scraping)
   Python + Flask (for serving scraped data)
   Docker (for containerization)
   AWS EC2 (for deployment)

# Setup Instructions  

1. Clone the Repository
            git clone https://github.com/alekyagandem/scraper-app.git
            cd scraper-app
2.  Build and Run the Docker Container
            docker build -t scraper-app .
            docker run -d -p 5000:5000 -e SCRAPE_URL="https://example.com" scraper-app

3.  Access the API
            http://<YOUR_EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:5000

